attributes.Long form description: The student carries out the change of the nintendo switch controls, change of game card and sd card as well as turning the equipment on and off.

attributes.Transcription: We are performing the task Nintendo switch.

attributes.Action sentence: The student inspects the parts of the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Transcription: Your first task is to change from handheld mode to the joy-con comfort grip pad.
Joy-con comfort grip pad.
Yes that's the one.
You first need to remove the colored joy-cons from the display.

attributes.Action sentence: The student assembles the joy-con controller and the comfort grip pad.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student was in the wrong place when sliding the joy con.
The student was in the wrong place when sliding the joy con.

attributes.Transcription: Very good.
Your next task is to change from the joy-con comfort grip pad to the two individual joy-cons.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the joy con controller from the comfort grip.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student tries to remove the Joy-Con, but fails.

attributes.Transcription: The best way to unlock the Joy-Con is by pushing the black button and pull up.

attributes.Action sentence: The student assembles the joy-con controller and the joy-con strap.

attributes.Transcription: Please make sure to align the black, the minus, and plus signs on the black part with the minus and plus sign on the color joy-con.
Now please lock joy-cons using the white trigger or button.

attributes.Action sentence: The student locks the joy-con controller.

attributes.Transcription: You need to pull into the other direction.
Yes, that's fine.
Very good.
Your next task is to change from the two individual joy-cons back to handheld mode.

attributes.Action sentence: The student assembles the joy-con controller with the display.

attributes.Transcription: Yes, proceed.
Very good.
Your next task is to open the kickstand of the Nintendo and put the Nintendo on the table.
Yeah, the kickstand is on the left side.
That is correct.
Please, close the kickstand and change the game card.

attributes.Action sentence: The student exchanges a game card.

attributes.Transcription: The game card is on the top part.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student could not insert the game card.

attributes.Transcription: Your next task is to change the micro SD card.

attributes.Action sentence: The student exchanges a micro SD Card.

attributes.Transcription: You need to open first the kickstand.
Very good.
Your next task is to turn on the Nintendo switch.

attributes.Action sentence: The student turns on the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Transcription: Your next task is to turn off the Nintendo switch completely.

attributes.Action sentence: The student turns off the Nintendo switch.

attributes.Transcription: Please select power options.
And turn off completely.
Your task is over and you can stop recording.
